{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584469","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584469"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:47:28+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:47:28+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14524"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14524","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14524"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.67,0.12,0.15,0.03,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7219"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112871"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7219","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7219"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14524"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94908"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"6854"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"17517"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17519"},{"type":"contributions","id":"46417"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112871","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/112871"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following veins drains into the internal thoracic veins?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Anterior intercostal veins","Left superior intercostal veins","Posterior intercostal veins","Bronchial veins","Oesophageal veins"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior intercostal veins\u003C/strong\u003E drain into the internal thoracic veins, located on both sides of the chest. They are involved in draining the mediastinum, as well as the anterior chest wall.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELeft superior intercostal veins\u003C/strong\u003E drain the second, third, and sometimes fourth posterior intercostal veins on the left side and empty into the left brachiocephalic vein.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPosterior intercostal veins\u003C/strong\u003E drain the posterior portions of the intercostal spaces and typically empty into the azygos venous system.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBronchial veins\u003C/strong\u003E drain the bronchi and bronchioles and empty into the azygos system or pulmonary veins.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOesophageal veins\u003C/strong\u003E drain the oesophagus and empty into the azygos system, left gastric vein, or other nearby veins.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The internal thoracic veins receive drainage from the anterior intercostal veins and mediastinal veins."],"references":["Netter, F. H. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: Classic Regional Approach-Ebook. 2022. Elsevier Health Sciences","Shahoud JS, Kerndt CC, Burns B. Anatomy, Thorax, Internal Mammary (Internal Thoracic) Arteries. [Updated 2023 Jul 24]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537337/","JR, Daly DT. Anatomy, Thorax, Azygos Veins. [Updated 2023 Jul 30]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK554430/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94908"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14524"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94908","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRe